From Tom Wetzel Subject Re Old Corvettes Low insurance In article Richard Newton II writes On a related note does this seem a sane price for a ' convertible Corvette in good condition How does one determine these things My CR Used Car magazine doesn't list ' corvettes Any net wisdom on what to look for what to avoid Thanks in advance Rich First of all you might want to join the VetteNet during your search acquisition of the sounds about right for a wrong engine condition This means that the car may not have significant investment value but could be an excellent driver and or hobby You will also want to get a copy of the Corvette Black Book Don't leave home to look at Vettes without Since you are contemplating spending you might want to invest a few hours in reading the Corvette Buyer's Guide and purchase Noland Adams' tape How to Buy a The tape shows you how to check for damage There are many many factors that will affect the value road worthiness and repair expense of your proposed The list is much too long to go into Join the VetteNet where there are over current Corvette owners many with vintage vettes that are available to help The pubs I mentioned above are available from Mid America Designs and several other Corvette parts Good luck Tom ' ' Cruiser